    <fr:title text="completeness of the subset construction › forest://jonmsterling/jms-00OE/0 › empty string"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00OE/0.xml" title="completeness of the subset construction › forest://jonmsterling/jms-00OE/0" addr="jms-00OE/0" type="local"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00OE.xml" title="completeness of the subset construction" addr="jms-00OE" type="local">completeness of the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-017T.xml" title="subset construction" addr="jms-017T" type="local">subset construction</fr:link></fr:link> › jms-00OE/0</fr:link> › empty string</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Case</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u=\epsilon ]]></fr:tex>, then we have assumed that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{M}\xRightarrow {\epsilon }q]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in F_{M}]]></fr:tex>; therefore, by definition, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in  s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>. Thus we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in  s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}\cap F_{M}]]></fr:tex> and so it follows by definition that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}\in  F_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
